3 Conclusions

In McCarthy-Jarvis2010 paper, MTLD and HD-D has a correlation of r = .800; MTLD and TTR r =.322; HD-D and TTR r = -.051 (N = 1584). In our results, MTLD and HD-D have the highest correlation (r = .714). Meanwhile, MTLD and TTR has r = .270, a bit lower than what M-J2010 reported. TTR and HDD are also modestly correlated (r = .426)

All of the measures suggest that the control group has higher lexical diversity than experimental group, with HD-D showing the biggest contrast and MTLD the smallest.
